This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with text chunking, which is a task in natural language processing. It could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as the paper discusses the performance of various systems that have taken part in the shared task. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as text chunking is a sub-task of natural language understanding, which is a key area of AI research. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as text chunking can be used to improve search results by identifying relevant phrases. Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) could also be a relevant sub-category as neural networks have been used for text chunking in the past.
